## §1 Auth / role enforcement

**Detected pattern**: {{AUTH_PATTERN}}

<!-- One of:
- Spring Security filter chain + @PreAuthorize on controllers
- SecurityConfig.requestMatchers().hasRole() (URL-based)
- Custom JWT validation filter
- Keycloak / Okta adapter
- Delegated to gateway (no in-service auth)
- No auth (internal-only service)
-->

**Rules:**
- {{AUTH_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Role checks live in `SecurityConfig.requestMatchers("/path").hasAnyRole("ROLE_A", "ROLE_B")` — declarative, not imperative.
- Do NOT read `SecurityContextHolder` inside service methods. If you need caller context, inject it as a parameter or use a method-level `@PreAuthorize`.
- Controllers are annotation-free for auth — rules live in `SecurityConfig` centrally.
-->

